## Assistant

I fixed the CI failure shown in the screenshot.

Root cause
- forge install --no-commit is not a valid flag for the Foundry version in GitHub Actions. The step failed during â€œInitialize submodules and install dependenciesâ€.

What I changed
- Removed the unsupported --no-commit flag from all workflows:
  - .github/workflows/ci.yml
  - .github/workflows/security.yml

Why this works
- forge install without flags will install submodule dependencies as expected. We already initialize git submodules before running it, so no extra flags are needed.

What you can do next
- Re-run the CI pipeline. The â€œInitialize submodules and install dependenciesâ€ step should pass now, allowing the workflow to proceed to build, test, coverage, and security scans.

If anything else fails in later steps, share the log snippet and Iâ€™ll patch it quickly.

