    "work_summary": "=== CODEREVIEW WORK SUMMARY ===\nTotal steps: 1\nFiles examined: 3\nRelevant files identified: 3\nMethods/functions involved: 0\nIssues found: 0\n\n=== WORK PROGRESSION ===\nStep 1: Scope: AMLSwapHook.sol, DeployV4PoolAndSeed.s.sol, AMLSwapHook.v4.t.sol. Review for quality, security, performance, and correctness vs Uniswap v4 BaseHook API.\n\nStrengths:\n- Hook now conforms to BaseHook via _beforeSwap override using PoolOperation.SwapParams and returns ZERO_DELTA, 0 dynamic fee.\n- onlyPoolManager guard is respected via BaseHook; tests simulate PoolManager with vm.prank.\n- Clear owner-only admin controls for blacklist, authorized tokens, conversion rate.\n- Explicit revert messages for zero-address and zero-rate updates.\n- Foundry config set to EVM Cancun; v4 remappings added; CI stabilized.\n\nConcerns & Recommendations:\n1) Token conversion inside hook (beforeSwap) risks and assumptions:\n   - Requires hook to be pre-funded with wINR; could be drained if conversionRates are misconfigured or approvals are too permissive.\n   - No max per-tx or per-user conversion cap inside hook; a separate conversion service exists elsewhere but hook path has none.\n   - No slippage or oracle; rates are static and admin-controlled; feasible for PoC, risky for production.\n   - Recommend: (a) add a configurable maxConversionPerTx; (b) add a simple circuit breaker boolean (conversionEnabled) to disable conversion quickly; (c) event emission path for conversion already present.\n\n2) Reentrancy and transfer ordering:\n   - Using SafeERC20 is good. For safety, avoid external ERC20 calls before completing all internal checks; current logic performs checks first then transfers which is OK.\n   - Consider a nonReentrant modifier if the hook will store state in more complex versions (currently no state changes during conversion besides transfers).\n\n3) Amount sign handling:\n   - AmountSpecified can be negative (exactOut). Code converts to absolute amount, which is